  "_stub_comment": "Remaining stubs: thai (44 consonants with many shared sounds + positional vowels + tone classes — not reducible to a simple unique letter→sound table; needs a purpose-built design) and han (not an alphabet). Both are still valid SOURCE scripts: `latin.sounds.thai` lets Thai speakers learn the Latin alphabet even though we cannot teach Thai.",
  "_sounds_comment": "letters[].sounds maps a SOURCE script → the letter's name written in that script (B → بي for an Arabic reader). Used by introScriptExercises via opts.srcScripts so the answer is readable to the learner; without it a Latin course would ask a non-Latin reader to pick 'b' from Latin choices. Values are the letter NAME (not the phonetic value) because phonetic values collide (c/k/q → ك) and would yield several correct MCQ answers. NATIVE REVIEW OWED on every column.",
